    "body": "### Problem\n\nRecent changes to the API (likely around multiple return value support in commit 0aa7d2f4d546) have broken the ability to retrieve return values from nvim_buf_call and nvim_win_call when executed within a Lua coroutine(which gitsigns.nvim uses for many of its operations, e.g. blame_line.).\n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nrun `nvim --headless -u NONE -S repro.lua -c \"q\"`\n\nNeovim version: 0.13.0\n\n--- Testing in Main Thread (Direct) ---\nnvim_buf_call result: 42 (Expected: 42)\nnvim_win_call result: hello (Expected: hello)\n\n--- Testing in Coroutine ---\nnvim_buf_call result: nil (Expected: 42)\nnvim_win_call result: nil (Expected: hello)\n\n\n\nrepro.lua\n\n```\nlocal function run_tests(context_name)\n    print(\"\\n--- Testing in \" .. context_name .. \" ---\")\n    \n    -- 1. Test nvim_buf_call\n    local buf_res = vim.api.nvim_buf_call(0, function()\n        return 42\n    end)\n    print(\"nvim_buf_call result: \" .. tostring(buf_res) .. \" (Expected: 42)\")\n\n    -- 2. Test nvim_win_call\n    local win_res = vim.api.nvim_win_call(0, function()\n        return \"hello\"\n    end)\n    print(\"nvim_win_call result: \" .. tostring(win_res) .. \" (Expected: hello)\")\nend\n\nprint(\"Neovim version: \" .. vim.version().major .. \".\" .. vim.version().minor .. \".\" .. vim.version().patch)\n\n-- Test 1: Outside coroutine (Direct call)\nrun_tests(\"Main Thread (Direct)\")\n\n-- Test 2: Inside coroutine\nlocal co = coroutine.create(function()\n    run_tests(\"Coroutine\")\nend)\n\nlocal ok, err = coroutine.resume(co)\nif not ok then\n    print(\"Coroutine error: \" .. tostring(err))\nend\n\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe functions should return the value(s) returned by the provided Lua function, matching the behavior outside of a coroutine.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-533+gd7164eced6\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nseems unrelated?\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narchlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nlocal build",
